# $XFree86: xc/config/cf/Library.tmpl,v 3.28 2006/07/18 03:05:29 tsi Exp $

         CC = i486-linux-gcc -pipe -Os -mtune=i386 -static -Wall -s -DNOERROR  -D__i386__

  CCOPTIONS =
STD_DEFINES = -Dlinux -D__i386__ -D_POSIX_SOURCE -D_POSIX_C_SOURCE=2 				-D_BSD_SOURCE -D_SVID_SOURCE 				-D_GNU_SOURCE -DX_LOCALE $(PROJECT_DEFINES)
CDEBUGFLAGS = -Os -fno-strength-reduce
CLIBDEBUGFLAGS =
     CFLAGS = $(CDEBUGFLAGS) $(CLIBDEBUGFLAGS) $(CCOPTIONS) $(THREADS_CFLAGS) $(ALLDEFINES)

LIBNAME = Xaw

all::
	$(_NULLCMD_)
	$(_NULLCMD_)
	@if [ -d unshared ]; then exit 0; else set -x; mkdir unshared; fi
	$(_NULLCMD_)

includes::
	$(_NULLCMD_)
	$(_NULLCMD_)
	@if [ -d unshared ]; then exit 0; else set -x; mkdir unshared; fi
	$(_NULLCMD_)

.c.o:
	$(_NULLCMD_)
	$(_NULLCMD_)
	$(RM) $@ unshared/$@
	 	$(CC) -c $(CCOPTIONS) $(THREADS_CFLAGS) $(ALLDEFINES) 	$(CDEBUGFLAGS) $(CLIBDEBUGFLAGS) $(_NOOP_) $*.c -o unshared/$@
	$(_NULLCMD_)
	$(RM) $@
	 	$(CC) -c $(CFLAGS) $(_NOOP_) $(SHLIBDEF) $(SHAREDCODEDEF) $(PICFLAGS) $*.c

.S.o:
	$(_NULLCMD_)
	$(_NULLCMD_)
	$(RM) unshared/$@ unshared/$*.i
	$(CPP)  -D__ELF__ $(ALLDEFINES) $(CDEBUGFLAGS) $(CLIBDEBUGFLAGS) $(_NOOP) $*.S | \
		grep -v '^\#' > unshared/$*.i
	$(AS) $(ASMOPTS) -o unshared/$@ unshared/$*.i
	$(RM) unshared/$*.i
	$(_NULLCMD_)
	$(RM) $@ $*.i
	$(CPP)  -D__ELF__ $(ALLDEFINES) $(_NOOP) $*.S | \
		grep -v '^\#' > $*.i
	$(AS) $(ASMOPTS) -o $*.o $*.i
	$(RM) $*.i

cleandir::
	$(_NULLCMD_)
	$(_NULLCMD_)
	-@if [ -d unshared ]; then \
		set -x; $(RM) -r unshared; else exit 0; fi
	$(_NULLCMD_)

all:: $(LIBPREFIX)$(LIBNAME).so.$(SOXAWREV)

$(LIBPREFIX)$(LIBNAME).so.$(SOXAWREV):  $(OBJS) $(EXTRASHAREDOBJS) $(EXTRALIBRARYDEPS)
	$(RM) $@~
	@set +e; S=`expr $(SOXAWREV) : '\([0-9]*\)'`; set -e; \
	SONAME=$(LIBPREFIX)$(LIBNAME).so.$$S; (set -x; \
		cd .; $(CC) -o ./$@~ $(SHLIBLDFLAGS) -Wl,-soname,$$SONAME $(OBJS) $(EXTRASHAREDOBJS) $(REQUIREDLIBS) ) || exit 1; \
		if [ $$SONAME != $@ ]; then (set -x; \
			$(RM) $$SONAME; $(LN) $@ $$SONAME); fi; \
		if [ -d $(BUILDLIBDIR) ]; then \
		:; \
	else \
		if [ -h $(BUILDLIBDIR) ]; then \
			(set -x; rm -f $(BUILDLIBDIR)); \
		fi; \
		(set -x; $(MKDIRHIER) $(BUILDLIBDIR)); \
	fi;\
	(set -x; $(RM) $(BUILDLIBDIR)/$$SONAME;\
	(cd $(BUILDLIBDIR) && $(LN) $(BUILDLIBTOP)/$(CURRENT_DIR)/$$SONAME .))
	$(RM) $@
	$(MV) $@~ $@
	@if $(SOSYMLINK); then (set -x; \
	  $(RM) $(LIBPREFIX)$(LIBNAME).so; \
	  $(LN) $@ $(LIBPREFIX)$(LIBNAME).so); fi
	@if [ -d $(BUILDLIBDIR)/. ]; then \
		set +x; \
	else \
		if [ -h $(BUILDLIBDIR)/. ]; then \
			(set -x; rm -f $(BUILDLIBDIR)/.); \
		fi; \
		(set -x; $(MKDIRHIER) $(BUILDLIBDIR)/.); \
	fi
	$(RM) $(BUILDLIBDIR)/$@
	cd $(BUILDLIBDIR)/. && $(LN) $(BUILDLIBTOP)/./$(CURRENT_DIR)/$@ .
	@if [ -d $(BUILDLIBDIR)/. ]; then \
		set +x; \
	else \
		if [ -h $(BUILDLIBDIR)/. ]; then \
			(set -x; rm -f $(BUILDLIBDIR)/.); \
		fi; \
		(set -x; $(MKDIRHIER) $(BUILDLIBDIR)/.); \
	fi
	@if $(SOSYMLINK); then (set -x; \
	  $(RM) $(BUILDLIBDIR)/$(LIBPREFIX)$(LIBNAME).so; \
	  cd $(BUILDLIBDIR)/. && $(LN) $(BUILDLIBTOP)/./$(CURRENT_DIR)/$(LIBPREFIX)$(LIBNAME).so .); fi

cleandir::
	@set +e; S=`expr $(SOXAWREV) : '\([0-9]*\)'`; set -e; \
	set -x; $(RM) $(LIBPREFIX)$(LIBNAME).so.$$S
	$(RM) $(LIBPREFIX)$(LIBNAME).so.$(SOXAWREV) $(LIBPREFIX)$(LIBNAME).so

install::
	@if [ -d $(DESTDIR)$(SHLIBDIR) ]; then \
		set +x; \
	else \
		if [ -h $(DESTDIR)$(SHLIBDIR) ]; then \
			(set -x; rm -f $(DESTDIR)$(SHLIBDIR)); \
		fi; \
		(set -x; $(MKDIRHIER) $(DESTDIR)$(SHLIBDIR)); \
	fi
	$(INSTALL) $(INSTALLFLAGS) $(INSTBINFLAGS) $(LIBPREFIX)$(LIBNAME).so.$(SOXAWREV) $(DESTDIR)$(SHLIBDIR)
	@set +e; S=`expr $(SOXAWREV) : '\([0-9]*\)'`; set -e; \
	T=$(DESTDIR)$(SHLIBDIR)/$(LIBPREFIX)$(LIBNAME).so.$$S; \
	  if [ $(SOXAWREV) != $$S ]; then (set -x; \
	    $(RM) $$T && $(LN) $(LIBPREFIX)$(LIBNAME).so.$(SOXAWREV) $$T); fi
	  @if $(SOSYMLINK); then (set -x; \
	  $(RM) $(DESTDIR)$(SHLIBDIR)/$(LIBPREFIX)$(LIBNAME).so; \
	  $(LN) $(LIBPREFIX)$(LIBNAME).so.$(SOXAWREV) $(DESTDIR)$(SHLIBDIR)/$(LIBPREFIX)$(LIBNAME).so); fi

all:: lib$(LIBNAME).a

lib$(LIBNAME).a: $(OBJS) $(EXTRAUNSHAREDOBJS) $(EXTRALIBRARYDEPS)
	$(RM) $@
	@(set -x; cd unshared && $(AR) ../$@ $(OBJS) $(EXTRAUNSHAREDOBJS)) || exit 1;
	$(RANLIB) $@
	@if [ -d $(BUILDLIBDIR)/. ]; then \
		set +x; \
	else \
		if [ -h $(BUILDLIBDIR)/. ]; then \
			(set -x; rm -f $(BUILDLIBDIR)/.); \
		fi; \
		(set -x; $(MKDIRHIER) $(BUILDLIBDIR)/.); \
	fi
	$(RM) $(BUILDLIBDIR)/$@
	cd $(BUILDLIBDIR)/. && $(LN) $(BUILDLIBTOP)/./$(CURRENT_DIR)/$@ .

install::
	@if [ -d $(DESTDIR)$(USRLIBDIR) ]; then \
		set +x; \
	else \
		if [ -h $(DESTDIR)$(USRLIBDIR) ]; then \
			(set -x; rm -f $(DESTDIR)$(USRLIBDIR)); \
		fi; \
		(set -x; $(MKDIRHIER) $(DESTDIR)$(USRLIBDIR)); \
	fi
	$(INSTALL) $(INSTALLFLAGS) $(INSTLIBFLAGS) lib$(LIBNAME).a $(DESTDIR)$(USRLIBDIR)
	$(RANLIB) $(RANLIBINSTFLAGS) $(DESTDIR)$(USRLIBDIR)/lib$(LIBNAME).a

lintlib:: llib-l$(LIBNAME).ln

llib-l$(LIBNAME).ln: $(SRCS) $(EXTRALIBRARYDEPS)
	$(RM) $@
	$(LINT) $(LINTLIBFLAG)$(LIBNAME) $(LINTFLAGS) $(SRCS)

install.ln::
	@if [ -d $(DESTDIR)$(LINTLIBDIR) ]; then \
		set +x; \
	else \
		if [ -h $(DESTDIR)$(LINTLIBDIR) ]; then \
			(set -x; rm -f $(DESTDIR)$(LINTLIBDIR)); \
		fi; \
		(set -x; $(MKDIRHIER) $(DESTDIR)$(LINTLIBDIR)); \
	fi
	$(INSTALL) $(INSTALLFLAGS) $(INSTLIBFLAGS) llib-l$(LIBNAME).ln $(DESTDIR)$(LINTLIBDIR)/llib-l$(LIBNAME).ln

includes:: $(HEADERS)
	@if [ -d $(BUILDINCDIR)/X11/Xaw ]; then \
		set +x; \
	else \
		if [ -h $(BUILDINCDIR)/X11/Xaw ]; then \
			(set -x; rm -f $(BUILDINCDIR)/X11/Xaw); \
		fi; \
		(set -x; $(MKDIRHIER) $(BUILDINCDIR)/X11/Xaw); \
	fi
	@(set -x; cd $(BUILDINCDIR)/X11/Xaw && for i in $(HEADERS); do \
		$(RM) $$i; \
		$(LN) $(BUILDINCTOP)/../../$(CURRENT_DIR)/$$i .; \
	done)

install:: $(HEADERS)
	@if [ -d $(DESTDIR)$(INCDIR)/X11/Xaw ]; then \
		set +x; \
	else \
		if [ -h $(DESTDIR)$(INCDIR)/X11/Xaw ]; then \
			(set -x; rm -f $(DESTDIR)$(INCDIR)/X11/Xaw); \
		fi; \
		(set -x; $(MKDIRHIER) $(DESTDIR)$(INCDIR)/X11/Xaw); \
	fi
	@for flag in ${MAKEFLAGS} ''; do \
	  case "$$flag" in *=*) ;; --*) ;; *[i]*) set +e;; esac; done; \
	for i in $(HEADERS); do \
		(set -x; $(INSTALL) $(INSTALLFLAGS) $(INSTINCFLAGS) $$i $(DESTDIR)$(INCDIR)/X11/Xaw); \
	done

lint:
	$(LINT) $(LINTFLAGS) $(SRCS) $(LINTLIBS)
lint1:
	$(LINT) $(LINTFLAGS) $(FILE) $(LINTLIBS)

MANSUFFIX = $(LIBMANSUFFIX)

all:: Xaw.$(MANNEWSUFFIX)

Xaw.$(MANNEWSUFFIX)::  Xaw.$(MANSRCSUFFIX)
	$(RM) $@
	 	$(RAWCPP)  $(MANDEFS) $(EXTRAMANDEFS) <Xaw.$(MANSRCSUFFIX) | sed -e '/^#  *[0-9][0-9]*  *.*$$/d' 			-e '/^#line  *[0-9][0-9]*  *.*$$/d' 			-e '/^#[ 	]*pragma[ 	]/d' 			-e '/^[ 	]*XCOMM$$/s/XCOMM/#/' 			-e '/^[ 	]*XCOMM[^a-zA-Z0-9_]/s/XCOMM/#/' 			-e '/^[ 	]*XHASH/s/XHASH/#/' 			-e '/\@\@$$/s/\@\@$$/\\/' >$@

cleandir::

depend:: $(DEPEND)

$(DEPEND):
	@echo "checking $@ over in $(DEPENDSRC) first..."; \
	cd $(DEPENDSRC) && $(MAKE) makedependonly; \
	echo "okay, continuing in $(CURRENT_DIR)"

depend::
	$(DEPEND) $(DEPENDFLAGS) -- $(ALLDEFINES) $(DEPEND_DEFINES) -- $(SRCS)

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------
# common rules for all Makefiles - do not edit

.c.i:
	$(RM) $@
	 	$(CC) -E $(CFLAGS) $(_NOOP_) $*.c > $@

.SUFFIXES: .S

.S.i:
	$(RM) $*.i
	$(CPP)  -D__ELF__ $(ALLDEFINES) $(_NOOP_) $*.S | \
		grep -v '^\#' > $*.i

.SUFFIXES: .ii

.cc.ii:
	$(RM) $@
	 	$(CC) -E $(CFLAGS) $(_NOOP_) $*.cc > $@

.SUFFIXES: .s

.c.s:
	$(RM) $@
	 	$(CC) -S $(CFLAGS) $(_NOOP_) $*.c

.cc.s:
	$(RM) $@
	 	$(CC) -S $(CFLAGS) $(_NOOP_) $*.cc

.SUFFIXES: .m

.m.o:
	$(CC) -c $(CFLAGS) -o $@ $<

Makefile:: $(IMAKE)

$(IMAKE) $(IMAKE).o:
	-@(cd $(IMAKESRC) && if [ -f Makefile ]; then \
	echo "checking $@ in $(IMAKESRC) first..."; $(MAKE) imakeonly; else \
	echo "bootstrapping $@ from Makefile.ini in $(IMAKESRC) first..."; \
	$(MAKE) -f Makefile.ini BOOTSTRAPCFLAGS="$(BOOTSTRAPCFLAGS)"; fi; \
	echo "okay, continuing in $(CURRENT_DIR)")

Makefile::
	-@if [ -f Makefile ]; then set -x; \
	$(RM) Makefile.bak; $(MV) Makefile Makefile.bak; \
	else exit 0; fi
	$(IMAKE_CMD) -DTOPDIR=$(TOP) -DCURDIR=$(CURRENT_DIR)
